        <body>
            <entry xml:id="entry_bolat" xml:lang="os">
                <form type="lemma"><orth>bolat</orth></form>
                <sense><sense><abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>сталь</q>
                        </abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>steel</q>
                        </abv:tr></sense><sense><abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>булат</q>
                        </abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>bulat (a steel alloy similar to Damascus steel)</q>
                        </abv:tr></sense></sense>
                <abv:exampleGrp>
                    <abv:example>
                        <quote>bolat ændonæj dyn skænʒæn jæ cæfxædtæ</quote>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>из булатной стали сделает ему (коню) подковы</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>[s/he] will make a horseshoe of bulat steel for it (a horse)</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_Коста"/><biblScope>70</biblScope></bibl>
                    </abv:example>
                    <abv:example>
                        <quote>arsy dæn-dægtæn myn bolatæj kond cættæ færæt</quote>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>для зубов медведя у меня готов стальной топор</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>I have a steel axe ready for bears' teeth</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_Čerm."/><biblScope>63</biblScope></bibl>
                    </abv:example>
                    <abv:example xml:lang="os-x-digor">
                        <usg><lang/></usg>
                        <quote>Bolat-Xæmic</quote>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>Булатный Хамиц</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>Steel Khæmits</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_СОПам."/><biblScope>II
                            8</biblScope></bibl>
                    </abv:example>
                    <abv:example>
                        <quote>Soslan festadi syǧdæg bolat</quote>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>Сослан стал из чистой булатной (стали)</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>Soslan became made of pure bulat (steel)</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_Нарт._сказ."
                            /><biblScope>66</biblScope></bibl>
                    </abv:example>
                    <abv:example xml:lang="os-x-digor">
                        <usg><lang/></usg>
                        <quote>mæ bolat kærdæn ceteni, mæ bolat ærcij geteni</quote>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>мои булатные ножницы в корзиночке, моя булатная игла (воткнута) в
                                холст</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>my bulat scissors are in a basket, my bulat needle (is stuck) into
                                the canvas</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_Iræf"/><biblScope>22</biblScope></bibl>
                    </abv:example>
                </abv:exampleGrp>
                <etym xml:lang="ru">Широко распространенное на переднем Востоке слово: <mentioned
                        xml:lang="fa"><lang/>
                        <w>pūlād</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="pal"><lang/>
                        <w>pūlavat</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ar"><lang/>
                        <w>fūlād</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="syr"><lang/>
                        <w>pld</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="trk-x-north"><lang/>
                        <w>bulat</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="mn"><lang/>
                        <w>bolot</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="mn"><w>bold</w></mentioned>
                    etc. Also here <mentioned xml:lang="ka"><lang/>
                        <w>poladi</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="xcl"><lang/>
                        <w>pʼotovatʼ</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="xcl"
                        ><w>potpʼatʼ</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ce"><lang/>
                        <w>bolat</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ru"><lang/>
                        <w>bulat</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="uk"><lang/>
                        <w>bulat</w></mentioned>. Первоисточник не установлен; по Ф. Е. Коршу
                            (<bibl><biblScope>%bДревности восточные IV, 1912%b</biblScope></bibl>),
                    слово идет из индийского. — Осетинское слово, как и русское, усвоено скорее
                    всего из тюркского. Старое скифское слово для ‘стали’ — *%iandān%i. См. <ref
                        type="xr" target="#entry_ændon"/>.%n<bibl><ref type="bibl"
                            target="#ref_Вс._Миллер._Gr."/><biblScope>9</biblScope></bibl>. —
                            <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_ОЯФ_I"
                        /><biblScope>84</biblScope></bibl>.</etym>
                <etym xml:lang="en">The word is widespread in Western Asia: <mentioned xml:lang="fa"><lang/>
                        <w>pūlād</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="pal"><lang/>
                        <w>pūlavat</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ar"><lang/>
                        <w>fūlād</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="syr"><lang/>
                        <w>pld</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="trk-x-north"><lang/>
                        <w>bulat</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="mn"><lang/>
                        <w>bolot</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="mn"><w>bold</w></mentioned>
                    etc. Here belong also <mentioned xml:lang="ka"><lang/>
                        <w>poladi</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="xcl"><lang/>
                        <w>pʼotovatʼ</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="xcl"
                        ><w>potpʼatʼ</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ce"><lang/>
                        <w>bolat</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ru"><lang/>
                        <w>булат</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="uk"><lang/>
                        <w>булат</w></mentioned>. The original source in not known; according to F.
                    E. Korsch (<bibl><biblScope>Drevnosti vostočnye IV, 1912</biblScope></bibl>),
                    the word comes from Indic. — The Ossetic word, as well as the Russian, is
                    adopted from Turkic. The old Scythian word for ‘steel’ is *%iandān%i. See <ref
                        type="xr" target="#entry_ændon"/>.%n<bibl><ref type="bibl"
                            target="#ref_Вс._Миллер._Gr."/><biblScope>9</biblScope></bibl>. —
                            <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_ОЯФ_I"
                        /><biblScope>84</biblScope></bibl>.</etym>
